translated: Dahl, Gustaf Johannes, architect, Tranås. Born on May 7, 1886 in Tranås to foreman Carl Petter Johansson and Ida Dahl. He passed his studentexamen in Linköping in 1906 and graduated from KTH (A) in 1910. He studied at the Academy of Fine Arts from 1912-1914. He worked as a draftsman for C. Westman at the city hall building agency in Stockholm from 1910-1911, S. Curman in 1911, Elis Benckert in 1912, Höög & Morssing architects' firm in 1913, and professor L. Tengbom from 1914-1916. He worked as an architect outside the government in building management from 1918, and was appointed chief architect in Tranås from 1939-1947. He had his own architectural office in Stockholm, now in Tranås. Some of his projects include a hotel in Insjön (1920), crematorium in Vetlanda (1935), restoration of Masreli-ez-vån. in Hotel östergötland in Stockholm (1924), restoration of over 100 churches, schools, town halls in Vetlanda, private residences, among others and was an architect for the entire 1910s. He was a member of the Swedish Engineering Association from 1907-1920, and a board member for section A from 1917-1919. He got married sometime in the 1910s.
